  "description": [
    "Along Freedoms Road By RUTH PERRY THALHEIMPR AWARD Every member of the NAACP in the Miami area is walking a little taller and holding hie head a little higher these days because of a national award given them recently in Detroit during the 48th annual national meeting of the organization The Thalheimer Award is a great honor given only after due deliberation of the work in civil rights of branches and state conferences at the local level throughout the country I believe it is the highest honor that could be given to local branches by the national body This citation should be a great incentive to all of us who are fighting for freedom in this area and I am sure we can hope for even greater strides forward in our civil rights work during the coming year LEADERSHIP QUALITIES This week I will give some fur ther suggestions on how to achieve firstclass citizenship Last week I wrote on the great need for Negro leadership Firt of all let us briefly take quick look at some general and specific quali ties good leaders should pocsess It is obvious that a good leader hould have the qualities he seeks to"
